==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic, from the same Indo-European base as [[foot]].  Cognate with Old Saxon ''*feter'' (Dutch [[veter]] ‘lace’), Old High German [[fezzera]] (obsolete German [[Fesser]]), Old Norse [[fjǫturr]].

